{"parse":{"title":"Metacosa Movement","pageid":54992262,"revid":816809599,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Metacosa</b> is an <a href=\"/wiki/Italian_art\" title=\"Italian art\">Italian art</a> movement founded in the late 1970s.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Metacosa_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The group was formed by <a href=\"/wiki/Giuseppe_Bertoloni\" title=\"Giuseppe Bertoloni\">Giuseppe Bartolini</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Giuseppe_Biagi_(painter)\" title=\"Giuseppe Biagi (painter)\">Giuseppe Biagi</a>, Gianfranco Ferroni, <a href=\"/wiki/Bernardino_Luino\" title=\"Bernardino Luino\">Bernardino Luino</a>, Sandro Luporini, <a href=\"/wiki/Lino_Mannocci\" title=\"Lino Mannocci\">Lino Mannocci</a> and Giorgio Tonelli.\n</p><p>The first exhibition was held in 1979 in <a href=\"/wiki/Brescia\" title=\"Brescia\">Brescia</a>, with the presentation of the critic Roberto Tassi who followed the activity also in the subsequent exhibitions. Other exhibitions were held in Milan, Viareggio, Bergamo and Vicenza.\n</p><p>The Metacosa has a figurative matrix of poetic intensity with accurate and calculated pictorial research. During his first exhibition in <a href=\"/wiki/Brescia\" title=\"Brescia\">Brescia</a> in 1979, Roberto Tassi wrote: \"<i>Every painter in this group has its own light, the quality and substance of light being different in each of them, the coincidence of poetics does not involve coincidence of style or poetry The fascination and the truth of the exhibition is precisely in this, in joining a common idea, and almost philosophy, painting, very different artists.</i>\"\n</p><p>In 2004, at the Oberdan Square in <a href=\"/wiki/Milan\" title=\"Milan\">Milan</a>, the exhibition <i>Methanoid Phenomenology</i> was held by Philippe Daverio.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Metacosa_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Italy), Palazzo Paolina (Viareggio (1983). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com.ng/books?id=2S03AAAAIAAJ&amp;q=Metacosa&amp;dq=Metacosa&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjHt5HT7-vVAhVGZFAKHRIqA50Q6AEIKTAA\"><i>La Metacosa: Giuseppe Bartolini, Giuseppe Biagi, Gianfranco Ferroni ... Giorgio Tonelli &#91;mostra, Viareggio, Palazzo Paolina, 18 agosto-4 settembre 1983&#93;</i></a> (in Italian). CEDIS.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=La+Metacosa%3A+Giuseppe+Bartolini%2C+Giuseppe+Biagi%2C+Gianfranco+Ferroni+...+Giorgio+Tonelli+%5Bmostra%2C+Viareggio%2C+Palazzo+Paolina%2C+18+agosto-4+settembre+1983%5D&amp;rft.pub=CEDIS&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft.aulast=Italy%29&amp;rft.aufirst=Palazzo+Paolina+%28Viareggio&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com.ng%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D2S03AAAAIAAJ%26q%3DMetacosa%26dq%3DMetacosa%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjHt5HT7-vVAhVGZFAKHRIqA50Q6AEIKTAA&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMetacosa+Movement\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com.ng/books?id=4aAUywAACAAJ&amp;dq=Metacosa&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjHt5HT7-vVAhVGZFAKHRIqA50Q6AEILzAB\"><i>Metacosa: giuseppe bartolini, giuseppe biagi, gianfranco ferroni, bernardino luino, sandro luporini, lino mannocci, giorgio tonelli</i></a>. PALAZZO PAOLINA. 1983.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Metacosa%3A+giuseppe+bartolini%2C+giuseppe+biagi%2C+gianfranco+ferroni%2C+bernardino+luino%2C+sandro+luporini%2C+lino+mannocci%2C+giorgio+tonelli&amp;rft.pub=PALAZZO+PAOLINA&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com.ng%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D4aAUywAACAAJ%26dq%3DMetacosa%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjHt5HT7-vVAhVGZFAKHRIqA50Q6AEILzAB&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMetacosa+Movement\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com.ng/books?id=APVOAAAAYAAJ&amp;q=Metacosa&amp;dq=Metacosa&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjHt5HT7-vVAhVGZFAKHRIqA50Q6AEINzAD\"><i>Sandro Luporini: metafisica del quotidiano&#160;; Immagini, parole e note nell'opera di Sandro Luporini&#160;: una raccolta di materiali e testi sul teatro di Giorgio Gaber e Sandro Luporini</i></a> (in Italian). ADAC. 2005.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abo